They also got weirdly excited when I mentioned where I worked.

originalText.text: I've been coming to this office for years, but they stopped taking my insurance. I called to see what other insurance they accept. The front desk  receptionist was really nasty. She asked that I text the insurance information, which obviously I don't have cause I'm trying to switch. After her attitude, I wouldn't want to be seen there.

originalText.text: The care I have received from Columbia Dental Clinic has been outstanding. I have been a patient of the clinic for over a year.  My dentist, Supraja, a Columbia Dental graduate student, worked with me to create a plan to address my teeth (I had 10+ cavities). She was welcoming, communicative, and helped educate me on how to improve my oral health at every turn. Prior to seeing Supraja, I had not had a cleaning in 4 years and had a good deal of dental phobia. I can credit her with not only resuscitating my teeth, but turning around my attitude toward dental care and dental health in general. The other hospital staff that I interacted with were professional and kind. As someone who does not have dental insurance, I am so grateful for the affordable and quality dental care that the Clinic provides. Would absolutely recommend.

Left plaque on my teeth after cleaning, no worries I won't be coming back I already scheduled another cleaning and root canal elsewhere after filing a grievance.

Should have left the second I saw tape on the light used to illuminate by the assistant . Maybe the doctor has better stuff I don't know because she didn't see me although she said she would that day right after the assistant.

The fact that foulguni had more interest in telling me prices than cleaning my teeth says a lot...pretty SADistic.

I kinda feel bad leaving a negative review I'm sure she needs the money maybe a go fund me for the lights and ripped up chairs and dirty vests that she probably got on Craigslist.

This place just has the typical gold digging disingenuous activity that goes on in the Heights. I've seen better places in The BRONX...And I'm from there.
